It is found in 2.1.2 EMF. I guess eclipse is supposed to refresh after installing a new plugin. The EMF had the same problem wuth 2.1.0 and 2.1.1
We know for a fact this build has been working well for a long time.  Did you run eclipse.exe -clean as I suggested?  Failing to do so will cause exactly this problem.

4)Started eclipse. 

Clean with out problems. I guess the class loader gets into problem while updating.I am a Senior J2EE Developer though.
May be it can be reproduced/fixed later. I am bringing down the Severity to low because this is reproducable in update/upgrade scenarios.
